nicipal elections|other municipalities and regional districts in British Columbia selected their new municipal governments]]. Voters elected a [[List of mayors of Vancouver|mayor]], 10 [[Vancouver City Council|city councillors]], 7 [[Vancouver Park Board|park board commissioners]], and 9 [[Vancouver School Board|school board trustees]] through [[plurality-at-large voting]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/candidate-101-what-expect-running-vancouver-city-council-1.4732911 |title=Candidate 101: City of Vancouver sets up info sessions for those mulling run for council |last=Correia |first=Cory |work=[[CBC News]]|date=July 4, 2018 |accessdate=July 24, 2018 }}</ref> Official registration for all candidates opened on September 4, 2018, and closed on September 14, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/bc-elections-nomination-period-begins-1.4810600|title=Nomination period begins for 2018 B.C. elections {{!}} CBC News|work=CBC|access-date=2018-09-24|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nFor the first time, candidates were listed in random order instead of alphabetical order. This was done in an effort to create a more even playing field for candidates, as research has shown many voters are more likely to vote for those listed first on a ballot, giving those candidates a perceived advantage over those lower down on the list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vancouver.ca/news-calendar/candidates-to-be-listed-in-random-order-on-2018-ballot.aspx|title=Candidates to be listed in random order on 2018 ballot|last=Vancouver|first=City of|date=2018-06-07|website=vancouver.ca|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>\n\n==Candidates and results==\n===Mayor===\nIncumbent [[Gregor Robertson (politician)|Gregor Robertson]], who had been mayor of Vancouver since being elected in 2008, announced on January 10, 2018, that he would not be running for reelection in the 2018 election.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://bc.ctvnews.ca/vancouver-mayor-gregor-robertson-won-t-seek-re-election-1.3753944|title=Vancouver Mayor Gregor Robertson won't seek re-election|last=Balca|first=Dario|date=2018-01-10|work=British Columbia|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>\n\nAt the close of nominations, 21 candidates had formally registered to run for mayor in the election.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/4166537/vancouver-bc-municipal-election-2018/|title=B.C. municipal election 2018: Vancouver|last1=Ferreras|first1=Jesse|date=June 30, 2018|work=[[Global News]]|accessdate=July 24, 2018|last2=Zussman|first2=Richard}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/vancouver-council-candidates-1.4770924 |title=A Vancouver voter's guide to city council's crowded ballot |first=Justin |last=McElroy |work=[[CBC News]] |date=August 2, 2018|accessdate=August 31, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://vancouversun.com/news/local-news/vancouver-election-heres-whos-running-for-city-council-in-2018|title=Vancouver election: Here's who's running for mayor of Vancouver in 2018|date=2018-02-28|work=Vancouver Sun|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref>\n\n{{Canadian election result/top|VAN|2018|List of mayors of Vancouver|Vancouver Mayor|percent=yes|elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|'''[[Kennedy Stewart (Canadian politician)|Kennedy Stewart]]''' |49,705 |28.71 |elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA| Ken Sim |48,748 |28.16 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Shauna Sylvester |35,457 |20.48 |elected=no}} \n{{CANelec|VAN|Coalition| [[Wai Young]] |11,872 |6.86 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|YES|[[Hector Bremner]] |9,924 |5.73 |elected=no}} \n{{CANelec|VAN|Van1st| Fred Harding |5,640 |3.26 |elected=no}} \n{{CANelec|VAN|Pro|David Chen |3,573 |2.06 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Sean Cassidy |1,536 |0.89 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|IDEA Vancouver|Connie Fogal |1,435 |0.83 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Mike Hansen |951 |0.55 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Jason Lamarche |695 |0.40 |elected=no}}\n{{