ng]]\n| leader_since4      = 2018\n| party4             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|Coalition|name}}\n| leaders_seat4      = Ran for Mayor ''(lost)''\n| last_election4     = N/A\n| seats4             = 0\n| seat_change4       = N/A\n| popular_vote4      = 11,872\n| percentage4        = 6.86%\n| swing4             = ''(Did not run)''\n| image5             = [[File:No image.svg|100px]]\n| color5             = FFD636\n| leader5            = [[Hector Bremner]]\n| leader_since5      = 2018\n| party5             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|YES|name}}\n| leaders_seat5      = Ran for Mayor ''(lost)''\n| last_election5     = pre-creation\n| seats5             = 0\n| seat_change5       = N/A\n| popular_vote5      = 9,924\n| percentage5        = 5.73%\n| swing5             = ''(Did not run)''\n| image6             = [[File:Adriane Carr of the Green Party.jpg|150x150px]]\n| color6             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|Green|nohash}}\n| leader6            = [[Adriane Carr]]<br />''(de facto)''\n| leader_since6      = 2011\n| party6             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|Green|name}}\n| leaders_seat6      = [[Vancouver City Council|Councillor]]\n| last_election6     = 1 seat, N/A\n| seats6             = 3\n| seat_change6       = {{increase}} 2\n| popular_vote6      = N/A\n| percentage6        = N/A\n| swing6             = N/A\n| image7             = \n| color7             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|COPE|nohash}}\n| leader7            = \n| leader_since7      = \n| party7             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|COPE|name}}\n| leaders_seat7      = \n| last_election7     = 0 seats, 9.24%\n| seats7             = 1\n| seat_change7       = {{increase}} 1\n| popular_vote7      = N/A\n| percentage7        = N/A\n| swing7             = N/A\n| image8             = \n| color8             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|OneCity|nohash}}\n| leader8            = \n| leader_since8      = \n| party8             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|OneCity|name}}\n| leaders_seat8      = \n| last_election8     = 0 seats, N/A\n| seats8             = 1\n| seat_change8       = {{increase}} 1\n| popular_vote8      = N/A\n| percentage8        = N/A\n| swing8             = N/A\n| image9             = [[File:Gregor Robertson Burrard.jpg|150x150px]]\n| color9             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|Vision|nohash}}\n| leader9            = [[Gregor Robertson (politician)|Gregor Robertson]]\n| leader_since9      = 2008\n| party9             = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|Vision|name}}\n| leaders_seat9      = [[List of mayors of Vancouver|Mayor]] <br /> ''(Not running for re-election)''\n| last_election9     = 7 seats, 45.97%\n| seats9             = 0\n| seat_change9       = {{decrease}} 7\n| popular_vote9      = N/A\n| percentage9        = N/A\n| swing9             = N/A\n<!-- map -->\n| map_image          = Stadtgliederung_Vancouver_2008.png\n| map_size           =\n| map_caption        = 23 official neighbourhoods of Vancouver (local usage varies)\n| title              = Mayor\n| before_election    = [[Gregor Robertson (politician)|Gregor Robertson]]\n| before_party       = {{Canadian party colour|VAN|Vision|name}}\n| after_election     = [[Kennedy Stewart (Canadian politician)|Kennedy Stewart]]\n| after_party        = Independent politician\n}}\n\nThe '''2018 Vancouver municipal election''' was held on October 20, 2018, the same day as [[2018 British Columbia municipal elections|other municipalities and regional districts in British Columbia selected their new municipal governments]]. Voters elected a [[List of mayors of Vancouver|mayor]], 10 [[Vancouver City Council|city councillors]], 7 [[Vancouver Park Board|park board commissioners]], and 9 [[Vancouver School Board|school board trustees]] through [[plurality-at-large voting]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/candidate-101-what-expect-running-vancouver-city-council-1.4732911 |title=Candidate 101: City of Vancouver sets up info sessions for those mulling run for council |last=Correia |first=Cory |work=[[CBC News]]|date=July 4, 2018 |accessdate=July 24, 2018 }}</ref> Official registration for all candidates opened on September 4, 2018, and closed on September 14, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/bc-elections-nomination-period-begins-1.4810600|title=Nomination period begins for 2018 B.C. elections {{!}} CBC News|work=CBC|access-date=2018-09-24|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nFor the first time, candidates were listed in random order instead of alphabetical order. This was done in an effort to create a more even playing field for candidates, as research has shown many voters are more likely to vote for those listed first on a ballot, giving those candidates a perceived advantage over those lower down on the list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vancouver.ca/news-calendar/candidates-to-be-listed-in-random-order-on-2018-ballot.aspx|title=Candidates to be listed in random order on 2018 ballot|last=Vancouver|first=City of|date=2018-06-07|website=vancouver.ca|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>\n\n==Candidates and results==\n===Mayor===\nIncumbent [[Gregor Robertson (politician)|Gregor Robertson]], who had been mayor of Vancouver since being elected in 2008, announced on January 10, 2018, that he would not be running for reelection in the 2018 election.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://bc.ctvnews.ca/vancouver-mayor-gregor-robertson-won-t-seek-re-election-1.3753944|title=Vancouver Mayor Gregor Robertson won't seek re-election|last=Balca|first=Dario|date=2018-01-10|work=British Columbia|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>\n\nAt the close of nominations, 21 candidates had formally registered to run for mayor in the election.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/4166537/vancouver-bc-municipal-election-2018/|title=B.C. municipal election 2018: Vancouver|last1=Ferreras|first1=Jesse|date=June 30, 2018|work=[[Global News]]|accessdate=July 24, 2018|last2=Zussman|first2=Richard}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/vancouver-council-candidates-1.4770924 |title=A Vancouver voter's guide to city council's crowded ballot |first=Justin |last=McElroy |work=[[CBC News]] |date=August 2, 2018|accessdate=August 31, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://vancouversun.com/news/local-news/vancouver-election-heres-whos-running-for-city-council-in-2018|title=Vancouver election: Here's who's running for mayor of Vancouver in 2018|date=2018-02-28|work=Vancouver Sun|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref>\n\n{{Canadian election result/top|VAN|2018|List of mayors of Vancouver|Vancouver Mayor|percent=yes|elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|'''[[Kennedy Stewart (Canadian politician)|Kennedy Stewart]]''' |49,705 |28.71 |elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA| Ken Sim |48,748 |28.16 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Shauna Sylvester |35,457 |20.48 |elected=no}} \n{{CANelec|VAN|Coalition| [[Wai Young]] |11,872 |6.86 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|YES|[[Hector Bremner]] |9,924 |5.73 |elected=no}} \n{{CANelec|VAN|Van1st| Fred Harding |5,640 |3.26 |elected=no}} \n{{CANelec|VAN|Pro|David Chen |3,573 |2.06 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Sean Cassidy |1,536 |0.89 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|IDEA Vancouver|Connie Fogal |1,435 |0.83 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Mike Hansen |951 |0.55 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Jason Lamarche |695 |0.40 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Rollergirl |686 |0.40 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Ping Chan | 653| 0.38 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|John Yano | 510| 0.29 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Tim Ly |349 |0.20 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Sophia C. Kaiser |336 |0.19 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Satwant K. Shottha |331 |0.19 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Lawrence Massey |233 |0.13 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Katy Le Rougetel |181 |0.10 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|G\u00f6l\u00f6k Z. Buday |178 |0.10 |elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Maynard Aubichon |139 |0.08 |elected=no}}\n{{end}}\n\n==== Formerly declared mayoral candidates ====\n* Patrick Condon ([[Coalition of Progressive Electors]]) withdrew from the race on July 13, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/patrick-condon-cope-stroke-1.4745821|title=Vancouver mayoral candidate Patrick Condon steps aside after stroke {{!}} CBC News|work=CBC|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>\n* [[Ian Campbell (Canadian politician)|Ian Campbell]] ([[Vision Vancouver]]) withdrew from the race on September 10, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://theprovince.com/news/local-news/vision-candidate-ian-campbell-withdraws-from-race-for-mayor-of-vancouver/wcm/fd157708-2ecf-4526-b985-78b58b5dfb39|title=Vision candidate Ian Campbell withdraws from race for mayor of Vancouver|date=2018-09-11|work=The Province|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>\n\n===City councillors===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Legend\n|-\n|'''Bold'''\n|denotes elected candidates\n|-\n| (I)\n| denotes incumbent city councillors\n|-\n| (O)\n| denotes incumbents of other municipal positions\n|}\n\n{{Canadian election result/top|VAN|2018|Vancouver City Council|percent=yes|elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Green| '''(I) [[Adriane Carr]]''' | 69,739 | 4.99|elected=yes }}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Green| '''[[Pete Fry]]'''|61,806 |4.42|elected=yes }}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA| '''(I) [[Melissa De Genova]]'''  | 53,251 | 3.81|elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|COPE| '''[[Jean Swanson]]'''| 48,865  | 3.50 |elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA| '''[[Colleen Hardwick]]'''| 47,747| 3.42|elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Green| '''(O) [[Michael Wiebe]]''' | 45,593| 3.26|elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|OneCity| '''[[Christine Boyle]]'''| 45,455 | 3.25 |elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA| '''(O) [[Lisa Dominato]]''' | 44,689 |3.20|elected=yes }}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA| '''[[Rebecca Bligh]]''' | 44,053| 3.15|elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA| '''(O) [[Sarah Kirby-Yung]]''' | 43,581| 3.12|elected=yes}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA| David Grewal| 41,913 | 3.00|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Green| David H. Wong| 40,887| 2.93|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Vision| (I) [[Heather Deal]]  | 39,529  | 2.83|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|COPE| Derrick O'Keefe| 38,305 | 2.74|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA|Justin P. Goodrich|37,917 | 2.71|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|COPE| [[Anne Roberts]]|36,531 |2.62|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|OneCity| Brandon O. Yan| 36,167|2.59|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|NPA| Jojo Quimpo | 34,601| 2.48|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Sarah Blyth| 29,456| 2.11|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Vision| Tanya Paz| 28,836|2.06|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Vision| Diego Cardona| 27,325| 1.96|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Vision|(O) Catherine Evans|25,124 |1.80|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|(O) Erin Shum| 23,331| 1.67|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Van1st| Ken Low | 21,908|1.57|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Adrian Crook |17,392 |1.25|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Vision| Wei Q. Zhang| 16,734| 1.20|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Coalition| Ken Charko|16,366 |1.17|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Coalition| James Lin |16,191 |1.16|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Wade Grant|15,422 |1.10|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|XX|Independent|Taqdir K. Bhandal| 15,326| 1.10|elected=no}} \n{{CANelec|VAN|Van1st| Elizabeth Taylor|15,184 |1.09|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Coalition| Penny Mussio| 14,886| 1.07|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|YES| Brinder Bains| 13,948| 1.00|elected=no}} \n{{CANelec|VAN|YES| Stephanie Ostler| 13,530| 0.97|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Coalition| Jason Xie| 13,424|0.96|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|YES| Glynnis C. Chan  |13,218 |0.94|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Coalition| Glen Chernen|13,148 |0.94|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Coalition|Morning Li| 12,614| 0.90|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Van1st| Nycki K. Basra|12,133 |0.87|elected=no}} \n{{CANelec|VAN|YES| Jaspreet Virdi| 12,124| 0.87|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|Coalition| Franco Peta| 11,193| 0.86|elected=no}}\n{{CANelec|VAN|YES| Phyllis Tang|11,9